title: Agent: Bolts' Harris hurt eye in fireworks incident
description: Najee Harris suffered an eye injury in a July 4 fireworks incident, but his agent said the Chargers running back "is fully expected to be ready for the upcoming NFL season."
author: Kris Rhim

title: Pelicans, Jones agree to 3-year, $68M extension
description: Pelicans forward Herb Jones has agreed to a three-year, $68 million contract extension with the franchise.
author: Shams Charania

title: Horner sacked by Red Bull
description: Christian Horner has been sacked as Red Bull team principal with immediate effect after 20 years in charge of the Formula 1 team.

title: Farrell on bench as Pollock starts for Lions against AUNZ Invitational XV
description: Owen Farrell has been included among the replacements with Henry Pollock restored to the starting XV for the British and Irish Lions’ game with an Australia and New Zealand Invitational XV in Adelaide on Saturday.

title: Mariners pitcher Bryan Woo is working on a no-hitter at Yankee Stadium through 6 innings
description: All-Star pitcher Bryan Woo is throwing a no-hitter for the Seattle Mariners through six innings against the New York Yankees on Thursday night. Woo opened the game by walking Jasson Domínguez and Trent Grisham, then retired 16 straight batters. After the walks, Woo struck out Aaron Judge and retired Jazz Chisholm Jr. on a double play.
author: LARRY FLEISHER

title: Photos: Best images from Thunder's 90-81 Summer League win over Nets
description: The best photos from the Oklahoma City Thunder's 90-81 Summer League win over the Brooklyn Nets.

title: England keep 'fingers crossed' on Stokes injury
description: Ollie Pope says England will keep their “fingers crossed” Ben Stokes has not suffered a serious injury after the captain struggled on the first day of the third Test against India at Lord’s.

title: The Wimbledon finalist who lost in qualifying last year
description: A year ago, Amanda Anisimova was doing her best to avoid thinking about Wimbledon after failing to qualify for the main draw. Now she has a final to prepare for.
